// Cyberlimbs (rulebook p.115 abbreviated, p.364-367 detailed).
//
// Foundational cyberware: Cyberarm (4 Option Slots) or Cyberleg
// (3 Option Slots). Many cyberlimb options can also be installed in a
// "meat" arm/leg as the only piece of cyberware in that limb (the
// "Can be installed as the only piece of Cyberware in a meat arm"
// annotation on pp.364-367). The catalog records the *foundational*
// requirement; the runtime install pipeline handles the meat-limb
// alternative.
//
// Coverings (Plastic, Realskinn, Superchrome) attach to a Cyberarm or
// Cyberleg without taking an Option Slot — modeled as
// `prerequisite_slug: Some("cyberarm" | "cyberleg")` is too narrow
// (either works). We pick `cyberarm` as the primary slug; the runtime
// install pipeline accepts the cyberleg alternative. The catalog
// description states the rule.
CyberwareFile(
    cyberware: [
        // ----- Cyberarm + Cyberarm options -----
        (
            slug: "cyberarm",
            display_name: "Cyberarm",
            category: Cyberlimb,
            install_difficulty: Hospital,
            humanity_loss: Rolled(fixed: 7, dice: (n: 2, die: D6, divisor: 1)),
            price: Expensive,
            price_eb: 500,
            option_slots: 4,
            slot_cost: 0,
            prerequisite_slug: None,
            effects: [],
            description: "Replacement arm. Does not have to be paired. A Cyberarm has 4 Option Slots for Cyberarm or Cyberlimb Options, and each comes pre-installed with a Standard Hand that doesn't cost any Humanity Loss or take up a Cyberarm Option Slot. See p.364.",
        ),
        (
            slug: "standard_hand",
            display_name: "Standard Hand",
